news.title: Ronshine China Holdings misses interest payments on two bonds
news.para: Ronshine has not made payment of $12.798 million interest on the 8.1% senior notes due June 2023, which became due and payable on June 9 and has a 30-day grace period to pay such interest, it said in a HKEx filing late on Sunday.

news.title: Bank of Baroda raises MCLR on select tenor loans by up to 15 basis points
news.para: The bank has approved the revision in Marginal Cost of funds based Lending Rate (MCLR) with effect from July 12, 2022, Bank of Baroda said in a regulatory filing on Monday.

news.title: Evergrande unit Hengda's onshore bondholders reject proposal to delay repayment
news.para: Hengda Real Estate Group Co Ltd, Evergrande's flagship onshore unit, said in a filing to the Shenzhen Stock Exchange it is in talks with bondholders to reach an acceptable agreement as soon as possible.

news.title: NBFCs, HFCs securitisation volumes almost doubled to Rs 33,000 crore in April-June: Report
news.para: The growth in volumes reflects a 1.9 times increase when compared to Rs 17,200 crore of securitised assets in Q1 FY22 and a 4.4 times increase compared to Rs 7,500 crore in Q1 FY2021, the report said.

news.title: Bank of Maharashtra cuts MCLRs across tenors by up to 0.35%
news.para: The bank has reviewed the marginal cost of funds-based lending rate (MCLR) with effect from July 11, 2022, Bank of Maharashtra said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Mumbai: 25% work left, Metro-3 has only Rs 100 crore of Japan's loan
news.para: Although JICA had agreed and has been waiting to release funds since early 2021, indecisiveness of the MVA government held it back despite reminders from the Japanese lending agency, reports Nauzer K Bharucha.

news.title: Jaipur development body to hire private developer to remodel Nehru Place
news.para: Now the design has become redundant, and shop owners have failed to garner business in this old, dilapidated building, said officials.

news.title: Chandigarh residents raise concerns, queries at grievance redressal camp
news.para: A total of 304 applicants raised their issues and queries at the two-day grievance redressal camp organised to take up pending applications related to the estate office.

news.title: SIT to probe 'cheating' by Vadodara-based builder
news.para: Cops swung into action after city police commissioner Shamsher Singh formed a special investigation team (SIT) to probe the accusations against Patel.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body is not serious about rainwater harvesting
news.para: However, the officials claimed that they have constructed rainwater harvesting wells in a few parks where people were complaining about waterlogging.

news.title: New Delhi Municipal Council gives till August 18 to residents to verify tax outgo
news.para: "The assessment list for the year 2022-23 is prepared on the basis of the tax returns filed by the owner, occupier and the lessee in the previous year (2021-22)," an official said.

news.title: Vadodara: Poor construction in JnNURM housing schemes raises concern
news.para: According to the data last uploaded on the VMC website, all but 1,226 of these houses have been allotted while the remaining too will also be allotted soon.

news.title: Construction equipment sales to breach the 2018 peak next year
news.para: “We expect to see a growth of roughly 10% this year, on the total market side. The growth is largely driven from segments like coal mining and handling,” Dimitrov Krishnan, Head, Volvo Construction Equipment said.

news.title: Fix public notices on Vasai-Virar buildings facing demolition orders: Bombay HC to VVMC
news.para: ​However, it sought demolition statistics for 2 years after petitioners' advocate Ajay Jaiswal said VVMC is not following a 2018 government resolution that directed planning authorities/corporations to file caveats before a civil court after passing demolition orders so that they will be heard.

news.title: Bengaluru: Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout allottees seek relief from BDA penalisation
news.para: As per the sale deed between the BDA and allottees, the latter have to construct houses within five years of allotment. The BDA can impose a penalty on those who fail to construct houses within five years of site allotment. As per the agreement, around 5,000 allottees have to pay the penalty for keeping the sites vacant for more than five years.
